 :tx/rationale "UNSOUNDNESS-LEDGER-6: No crash-recovery test. LiveStore (live_store.rs, 1028 LOC) claims crash safety via append-only EDN transaction files with fsync. The architecture is: (1) write_tx() writes EDN to txns/ directory with fsync, then applies datoms in-memory. (2) flush() serializes store.bin. (3) On next open, recovery replays all txn files not already reflected in store.bin. This design is sound, but it has NEVER been tested. No test simulates: kill process mid-write, verify recovered store equals pre-crash state. No test verifies: corrupt txn file is handled gracefully (partial write). No test verifies: store.bin + txn files produces the same store as txn files alone (the store.bin is an optimization, not the source of truth). Additionally, the multi-writer race on store.bin is untested: two processes open same .braid, both write txn files, second flush overwrites first's store.bin. Txn files are preserved (no data loss) but store.bin is inconsistent. Next open replays txn files, but if replay logic has a bug, stores diverge silently. The fix is: (1) crash-recovery test: write N txns, delete store.bin, reopen, verify store.datoms() == original. (2) partial-write test: write corrupt bytes to a txn file, verify graceful error handling. (3) multi-writer test: interleave two LiveStore instances on same directory."
